Hernandéz et al . 2013
;
Gondim et al . 2014
). Depth range: 0–69 m ( Clark & Downey, 1992 ).

Color in life. Variable. In juveniles the abactinal surface is usually mottled with green, brown, beige and gray, whilst adults are yellow, brown, or orange on the abactinal surface. The actinal region is beige or yellowish in both, juveniles and adults ( Ummels, 1963 ;
Hendler et al . 1995
). Trindade specimens ( Figure 8 A–C).
